cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.LG

This paper deals with image analysis and segmentation using multi-spectral computed tomography data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the impact of reconstruction artefacts and segmentation controls, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of machine learning algorithms for segmentation, such as fast adaptive mean shift and unconstrained graph cuts, indicates that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
